<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEMS DIAGNOSTICS - Circuit Diagnostics -
        Injection Pressure Regulator (IPR)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Injection Pressure Regulator (IPR)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <figure id="f24007" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="D3320" filename="../figD33/D3320.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>Function Diagram for the Injector Pressure Regulator (IPR)</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The Function Diagram for the IPR includes the following:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Injection Pressure Regulator (IPR)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Engine Oil Temperature (EOT) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Injection Control Pressure (ICP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Manifold Absolute Pressure (MAP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Barometric Pressure (BAP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Camshaft Position (CMP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Crankshaft Position (CKP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Accelerator Position / Idle Validation (APS/IVS) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Electronic Control Module (ECM)</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <title>Function</title>
            </para>
            <para>The IPR valve controls oil pressure in the high pressure injection control system that actuates the
                injectors. The IPR valve consists of a solenoid, poppet, and a spool valve assembly. The IPR is mounted
                on the top rear of engine in the high pressure oil pump cover. The ECM regulates ICP by controlling the
                ON/OFF time of the IPR solenoid. An increase or decrease in the ON/OFF time positions the poppet and
                spool valve inside the IPR and maintains pressure in the ICP system or vents pressure to the oil sump
                via the rear cover.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The engine may not operate with an IPR fault, depending on the mode of failure.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>IPR Circuit Operation</title>
            <figure id="f24007" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="D3321" filename="../figD33/D3321.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
                <caption>IPR Circuit Diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The IPR valve is supplied with voltage from V
                <subscript>IGN</subscript>
                at terminal 1 of the IPR connector. The control of the injection control system is gained by the ECM
                grounding terminal 2 of the IPR valve through PIN X1-12 of the ECM. Precise control is gained by varying
                the percentage of ON/OFF time of the IPR solenoid. A high duty cycle indicates a high amount of
                injection control pressure is being commanded. A low duty cycle indicates less pressure being commanded.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Fault Detection / Management</title>
            </para>
            <para>An open or short to ground in the EGR control circuit can be detected by an on demand output circuit
                check during KOEO Standard tests. If there is a circuit fault detected a DTC will be set. When the
                engine is running, the ECM can detect if the injection control pressure is equal to the desired
                pressure. When the measured injection control pressure does not compare to the desired pressure, the ECM
                will ignore the measured ICP signal and controls the engine with the desired value.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>IPR Diagnostic Trouble Codes (DTCs)</title>
            </para>
            <para>DTCs are read using the Electronic Service Tool (EST) or by counting the flashes from the amber and
                red ENGINE lamp.
            </para>
            <verbatim id="f240dtc241">
                <line>
                    <emph type="bold">DTC 241</emph>
                </line>
                <line>
                    <emph type="bold">Output Circuit Check (OCC)</emph>
                </line>
            </verbatim>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>DTC 241 is set by the ECM when the OCC test has failed after the KOEO Standard test has been
                        run.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>DTC 241 can be set when a poor connection to the IPR solenoid or defective IPR coil exists.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>When DTC 241 is active the engine will not run and the amber ENGINE lamp will not be
                        illuminated.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <title>Tools</title>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Electronic Service Tool (EST) with Master Diagnostics software</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>International&#174; EZ-Tech Interface Cable</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Digital Multimeter (DMM)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Breakout box</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Breakout harness</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Terminal Test Adapter Kit</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>The IPR circuit requires the use of vehicle circuit diagrams. See truck Chassis Electrical Circuit
                Diagram manual for circuit numbers, connector and fuse locations.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>IPR Pin Point Diagnostics</title>
            <figure id="f24007" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="D3321" filename="../figD33/D3321.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
                <caption>IPR Circuit Diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="te24007069" tblwidth="pg-wide" frame="topbot">
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">IPR Voltage Checks</emph>
                                    (Check with regulator connector disconnected, breakout harness installed, and
                                    ignition Key ON.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>1 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>B+</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>IPR power from V
                                    <subscript>IGN</subscript>
                                    - If no voltage, check from fuse to IPR connector. See truck Chassis Electrical
                                    Circuit Diagram manual for circuit numbers, connector and fuse locations.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>0- 0.25V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If >0.25V, control wire is shorted to V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    or B+.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Connector Resistance Checks to Chassis Ground</emph>
                                    (Check with IPR connector disconnected, ignition key OFF, and negative battery cable
                                    disconnected.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>1 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>>1k&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Resistance to chassis ground. If &#60;1k&#x2126;, check for short to ground in
                                    circuit (check with fuse removed)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>>1k&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If &#60;1k&#x2126;, check for short to ground</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Harness Resistance Checks</emph>
                                    (Install breakout box on engine harness only. Check with fuse removed.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>X1-12 to fuse</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>5-20&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Resistance through entire IPR circuit including regulator, check with harness
                                    connected to IPR
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Fuse to 1</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>&#60;5&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If >5&#x2126; IPR power is open</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>X1-12 to 2</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>&#60;5&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If >5&#x2126; IPR control wire is open</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">IPR Diagnostic Trouble Code</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>DTC 241 = Output Circuit Check detected during Standard Test, indicates high or
                                    low resistance in circuit.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
